npm config set save=true (spare --save when doing npm install)
gulpfile.js should be able to used by other projects
add the following line in the <header> tage of your index.ejs 

    <!-- bower:css -->   
    <!-- endbower -->

    <!-- bower:js -->   
    <!-- endbower -->

    <!-- inject:css --> 
    <!-- endinject -->
    
    <!-- inject:js -->
    <!-- endinject -->

npm install --save-dev gulp
npm install -g gulp
standard folder structure for all porject so the gulpfile works for all

add the below lines following by dependencies {}

'overrides': {
    'bootstrap': {
        'main': [
            'dist'/js/bootstrap.js',
            'dist/css/bootstrap.min.css'
        ]
    },
    'font-awesome': {
        'main': [
            'css/font-awesome.min.css'
        ]
    }
}